articles.description: Members of the Michigan State faculty voted 61-4 to express no confidence in the eight-member governing body at the university. Meanwhile, the institution's interim president wrote to the campus community about cooperation with ongoing investigations.
articles.headline: Michigan State faculty delivers no-confidence vote on board of trustees

images.caption: The Michigan State faculty's vote against the board of trustees came largely in response to the board's decision to name John Engler the school's interim president.
images.name: John Engler [600x400] - Copy (2)

images.caption: Michigan State students, including one who jumped onto and sat on the middle of a table, interrupt an MSU board of trustees meeting to protest the school's selection of John Engler as the interim president.
images.name: MSU students vent frustration over interim president selection

videos.description: Quentin Goodwin feeds a pass to Tyrique Jones who powers in a two-handed slam.
videos.headline: Jones abuses the rim on dunk

videos.description: Xavier's Trevon Bluiett dishes a nice pass then later spins around a defender for a difficult jump shot.
videos.headline: Bluiett uses a nifty spin to set up a jumper

videos.description: Jon Elmore creates contact and still makes the difficult layup as Marshall goes on a 10-0 scoring run early in the second half.
videos.headline: Elmore makes tough layup to add to Marshall's 10-0 run

videos.description: Jon Elmore slices through the Xavier defense for a layup with some fancy footwork.

videos.description: Kerem Kanter rises up for graceful layup plus the foul.
videos.headline: Kanter drives for finger roll and-1

videos.description: Kerem Kanter leads the charge for Xavier with 16 points with 13 rebounds as the Musketeers beat the Marshall Thundering Herd, 81-77.
videos.headline: Five Musketeers score in double figures as No. 9 Xavier pulls away
